
Install RVM with Ruby and Rails: https://rvm.io/rvm/install
    \curl -L https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable --rails

Install git if it is not installed already.
    # if you do not have homebrew here is a fast way to get it: (http://mxcl.github.com/homebrew/)
    ruby -e "$(curl -fsSkL raw.github.com/mxcl/homebrew/go)"
    brew install git

Install and launch PostgreSQL from: http://postgresapp.com

# connect to your postgres sever
psql -h localhost
  create database dgidb;
# quit your psql session
  \q

# check out the code
git clone git://github.com/genome/dgi-db.git
cd dgi-db

#install gem dependencies
bundle install

#load the database with the dgi schema
rake db:schema:load

#load the data into your database
psql -h localhost -d dgidb -f db/data.sql

#launch your development server
rails s

